#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:2
msgid "pytest-2.4.2: colorama on windows, plugin/tmpdir fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:4
msgid "pytest-2.4.2 is another bug-fixing release:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:6
msgid ""
"on Windows require colorama and a newer py lib so that py.io."
"TerminalWriter() now uses colorama instead of its own ctypes hacks. (fixes "
"issue365) thanks Paul Moore for bringing it up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:10
msgid ""
"fix \"-k\" matching of tests where \"repr\" and \"attr\" and other names "
"would cause wrong matches because of an internal implementation quirk (don't "
"ask) which is now properly implemented. fixes issue345."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:14
msgid ""
"avoid tmpdir fixture to create too long filenames especially when "
"parametrization is used (issue354)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:17
msgid ""
"fix pytest-pep8 and pytest-flakes / pytest interactions (collection names in "
"mark plugin was assuming an item always has a function which is not true for "
"those plugins etc.) Thanks Andi Zeidler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:22
msgid ""
"introduce node.get_marker/node.add_marker API for plugins like pytest-pep8 "
"and pytest-flakes to avoid the messy details of the node.keywords  pseudo-"
"dicts.  Adapted docs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:27
msgid ""
"remove attempt to \"dup\" stdout at startup as it's icky. the normal "
"capturing should catch enough possibilities of tests messing up standard FDs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:31
msgid ""
"add pluginmanager.do_configure(config) as a link to config.do_configure() "
"for plugin-compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:34
msgid "as usual, docs at http://pytest.org and upgrades via::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:36
msgid "pip install -U pytest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.4.2.rst:38
msgid "have fun, holger krekel"
msgstr ""
